{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3909 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3909 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[598,618],"content":"Compiler Error C3909","linkify":"Compiler Error C3909","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3909","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"aWinRT or managed event declaration must occur in a WinRT or managed type","pos":[619,692]},{"content":"A Windows Runtime event or managed event was declared in a native type.","pos":[699,770]},{"content":"To fix this error, declare events in Windows Runtime types or managed types.","pos":[771,847]},{"pos":[854,937],"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>event<ept id=\"p1\">](../../windows/event-cpp-component-extensions.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information, see [event](../../windows/event-cpp-component-extensions.md)."},{"content":"The following sample generates C3909 and shows how to fix it:","pos":[944,1005]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3909 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3909\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3909\"\nms.assetid: 0a443132-e53f-42dc-a58b-f086da3e7bfd\ncaps.latest.revision: 10\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3909\naWinRT or managed event declaration must occur in a WinRT or managed type  \n  \n A Windows Runtime event or managed event was declared in a native type. To fix this error, declare events in Windows Runtime types or managed types.  \n  \n For more information, see [event](../../windows/event-cpp-component-extensions.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates C3909 and shows how to fix it:  \n  \n```  \n// C3909.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr /c  \ndelegate void H();  \nclass X {  \n   event H^ E;   // C3909 - use ref class X instead  \n};  \n  \nref class Y {  \n   static event H^ E {  \n      void add(H^) {}  \n      void remove( H^ h ) {}  \n      void raise( ) {}  \n   }  \n};  \n```"}